(371, 1, 'ZIPP 404 NSW CARBON TUBELESS FRONT WHEEL', '&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;The Zipp 404 NSW Tubeless Carbon Clincher is an expansion of their cutting-edge NSW line. NSW is the acronym for Nest Speed Weaponry, a secure area within Zipp where they create the designs that eventually become wheels. The 404, as always is the all-round wheelset that tends toward rolling hills and flatter riding. And it keeps the 58mm depth that has been around for years.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;What is dramatically different is the rim width at the tire channel. It’s 26.4mm wide to provide a 19mm internal channel. That, when combined with their 27mm max width a little farther down the rim, means the shape has been aero optimized for 25mm tires.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;And those tires can be tubed or tubeless. The channel has been designed with tubeless in mind and is supplied with tape and valves.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: Prox