(361, 1, 'ZIPP 808 NSW DISC TUBELESS CLINCHER REAR WHEEL', '&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block-start: 1em; margin-block-end: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Now that triathlon and time trial bikes are built around disc brake wheels, Zipp knew they needed to optimize their 808 wheelset for the benefits and rigors of disc braking. The result is the 808 NSW Disc Tubeless Clincher.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block-start: 1em; margin-block-end: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;The 808 wheelset is super speedy. Many prefer an 808 back to a disc wheel, as it’s lighter and easier to control in crosswinds. Some folks like to run double 808’s, while other run an 808 in back with a shallower front wheel, like a Zipp 404. Either way, you’re getting a wheel that is best on flat roads and constant speeds, though strong road racers might also find it a great wheel for flattish road races and crits.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block-start: 1em; margin-block-end: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;This 404’s depth is 82mm, which has been the depth of the 404 for years. The width has changed for these wheels, with a max width of 26.4mm, an internal width of 19mm, and optimized for 25mm tires. They figure the bike you put these wheels on will probably be ridden almost entirely on pavement, and thus the benefits of a narrower tire come into play. It’s lighter and since you don’t need the same air cushion, there’s no reason to carry around the wide tire carcass. You can go wider if you want, but probably go no narrower than 23mm.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block-start: 1em; margin-block-end: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;But the change in width also comes with a second change. The extending of the SawTooth dimpling pattern all the way to the rim edge. As you should know by now, SawTooth is a design of indents molded into the outside rim walls that is comprised of twelve nodes. These are designed to start working for you at speeds of 20mph and then work better when faster. They essentially change the behavior of the wind around the rim to minimize side wind pressure on the rim in crosswinds, thus making the wheel more stable at high speeds.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block-start: 1em; margin-block-end: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;The interior of the rim has been changed as well. There is not only a bead hook at the end of the rim, but a ridge running below it, to better hold the bead of tubeless tires. This is to improve the interface with tubeless tire beads. This improves the sealing of the tire to the rim, which is a plus for safety and security. Factory-applied tubeless rim tape finishes the rim package.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block-start: 1em; margin-block-end: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Thanks to the need to make the rim sidewalls strong enough to handle the pressure of clincher tires, these carbon rims are super-strong. Stronger than aluminum rims, so worry not about their durability. They are race light, but training wheel tough.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block-start: 1em; margin-block-end: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Sapim CX-Ray J-Bend spokes are used both front and rear to lace the rim to the hub. These spokes are light, aero, and stiff. 24 spokes, two-cross, both front and rear.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block-start: 1em; margin-block-end: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;These NSW wheels utilize Zipp’s Cognition hubs. The front features scalloped flanges for the spoke beds. J-bend spokes resist the twisting forces disc-braking can put on spokes. This results in&amp;nbsp; less pressure on the spokes, increasing lateral stiffness and durability. The rear has a pawl design with an Axial Clutch, which reduces pawl drag by 50% when coasting, and with a 36-tooth engagement, you’re driving the wheel the moment you start pedaling.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block-start: 1em; margin-block-end: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;The disc-mounting method is Centerlock only. Lock ring not included. The hubs come with Zipp’s Tangente quick release skewers as well as&amp;nbsp; hand-removable end caps to fit 100x12mm and 100x15mm thru-axles in front and 142x12mm rear thru-axles.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block-start: 1em; margin-block-end: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;The wheels weigh in at 1860g per set, 910g in front, 950g in back.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block-start: 1em; margin-block-end: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;The wheels, sold separately as front and rear, also come with a wheel bag, a Zipp tubeless valve factory-installed, valve core removal tool, Zipp Cognition Oil, and a freehub body spacer to take the 11-speed hub down to 10-speed if you need. The single wheel bags can be secured together if you have a pair. SRAM/Shimano and Campagnolo 11-speed cassette bodies are standard; a SRAM XD-R driver can be swapped in as well.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block-start: 1em; margin-block-end: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;In case you’re wondering, yes, you can use standard clincher tires and tubes. You’ll just need to remove the tubeless valve.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block-start: 1em; margin-block-end: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;The Zipp 808 NSW Disc Tubeless Clincher is the wheel that meshes perfectly with the latest generation of disc brake triathlon and time trial bikes.&lt;/p&gt;', '', 'ZIPP 808 NSW DISC TUBELESS CLINCHER REAR WHEEL', 'buy ZIPP 808 NSW DISC TUBELESS CLINCHER REAR WHEEL from Toracycles 100% Original', 'ZIPP 808 NSW DISC TUBELESS CLINCHER REAR WHEEL'),
(369, 1, 'ZIPP 808 FIRECREST CARBON CLINCHER REAR WHEEL', '&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block-start: 1em; margin-block-end: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;The faster you go, the more a deeper rim helps. The Zipp 808 Firecrest Carbon Clincher is a deep as you can go short of a disc wheel, 82mm. But it might be faster, because it is far more stable in crosswinds, and you’ll feel comfortable enough to ride them in your next tri’, time trial, or flattish road race regardless of wind conditions.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block-start: 1em; margin-block-end: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;This iteration of Firecrest sees a heap of innovative Zipp designs come from their cutting-edge NSW lineup. The brake track has been upgraded to the ShowStopper textured braking surface. This is the 317 curved, vertical grooves on each side on the brake track that help move water off the surface and reduce stopping distances. In the wet or dry, this surface brakes as well as the best aluminum rims on the market.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block-start: 1em; margin-block-end: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;This is a serious refinement of the Firecrest shape. It’s blunt on the spoke side, with only slightly curved walls on the way to the brake track. The width at the brake track is 26mm, which is also as wide as the rim gets. The inner width of the rim is 17mm and the outer walls of the rim curve slightly from the spoke bed to the sidewalls, which means that the best aero tire choice leans toward 25mm tires. In addition to refining the shaping, Zipp has trickled down the ABLC SawTooth dimple pattern from their NSW wheels. It improves aerodynamics in no wind situations and it has been proven to be much better than the older version at reducing loads created by crosswinds. Riding these on gusty days will be controllable and confidence boosting.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block-start: 1em; margin-block-end: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Weight has also been reduced. They were able to cut 55g of weight from the set, down to 1830 for the two wheels; 830g for the front, 1000g for the rear. These wheels can’t be climber light, but any weight savings is a plus when you’re going uphill or accelerating.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block-start: 1em; margin-block-end: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;They also added their 77/177 hubset to the rims. The 18/24 hubs feature straight-pull Sapim CX-Sprint spokes, with the front radial and the rear two-cross. The rear hub has cassette body options: a SRAM 10/11-speed cassette body, a Campagnolo-compatible 10/11-speed body, and or a SRAM XDR driver body for wider-ranging cassette options, including 1x 10-42 cassettes.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block-start: 1em; margin-block-end: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;The Zipp 808 Firecrest Carbon Clincher wheels come with Zipp’s Tangente Platinum Evo brake pads, rim strips, Zipp valve extenders, and quick releases. The quick releases have wide lever bodies to reduce pressure in your palm and are designed to sit nearly flush with the frame when closed.&lt;/p&gt;', '', 'ZIPP 808 FIRECREST CARBON CLINCHER REAR WHEEL', 'buy ZIPP 808 FIRECREST CARBON CLINCHER REAR WHEEL from Toracycles 100% original', 'ZIPP 808 FIRECREST CARBON CLINCHER REAR WHEEL'),
(370, 1, 'ZIPP 303 NSW CARBON TUBELESS REAR WHEEL', '&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block-start: 1em; margin-block-end: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;While the Zipp 303 NSW is an expansion of the NSW line. They needed to push farther, and the result is this 303 NSW Tubeless Carbon Clincher. It’s faster and more flexible than the Firecrest, and the 303 itself is the depth and weight that appeals most to all-round riding, light enough for extended climbing, deep enough to speed on the flats.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block-start: 1em; margin-block-end: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Two things that are different right away are the new 19mm internal rim width and the tubeless channel. With the 19mm size, they’ve optimized the rim for 25mm tires. The tubeless channel means you have the option to run either tubed or tubeless tires.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block-start: 1em; margin-block-end: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;The 19mm width dictates a different rim shape than Firecrest. The depth remains at 45mm, the brake track at 26.4mm, but the widest spot is 26.5mm a bit of the way down the rim wall. This is to make sure 25mm tires are the most aero.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block-start: 1em; margin-block-end: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;The rim comes with Zipp’s ABLC SawTooth&amp;nbsp; dimple pattern. It improves aerodynamics in “no wind” (aka headwind) situations, but it’s greatest strength is reducing loads created by crosswinds. You’ll have no concerns piloting these wheels on gusty days, even if you’re small and riding aero bars. It’s almost like a traditional box-section clincher. Overall, the wheel is faster in all wind conditions.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block-start: 1em; margin-block-end: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;The brake track is Zipp’s ShowStopper textured braking surface. This is the 317 curved, vertical grooves on each side of the brake track that help move water off the surface and reduce stopping distances. In the wet or dry, this surface brakes as well as the best aluminum rims on the market.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block-start: 1em; margin-block-end: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Zipp’s Cognition hubs are deployed for the central movement. It utilizes a flangeless, radial front hub and a minimal, flanged rear hub that features two-cross spoking on both sides. The flanges are designed to be as light as possible without sacrificing strength. The rear hub utilizes Zipp’s Axial Clutch pawl mechanism, which reduces drag when coasting. The mechanism is on three cassette body choices: a SRAM 10/11-speed cassette body, a Campagnolo-compatible 10/11-speed body, and or a SRAM XDR driver body for wider-ranging cassette options, including 1x 10-42 cassettes. Spokes are the light and aero and strong Sapim CX-Ray.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block-start: 1em; margin-block-end: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Weight is 1500g for the set, 675g front, 825g rear.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom: 20px; margin-block-start: 1em; margin-block-end: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.9em; font-family: ProximaNova-Light, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;The Zipp 303 NSW Tubeless Carbon Clincher wheels come with: Zipp Tangente quick releases, Zipp wheel bags, Zipp tubeless tape and valve factory-installed, valve core removal tool, Cognition Oil for rear hub, and cassette body spacer.&lt;/p&gt;', '', 'ZIPP 303 NSW CARBON TUBELESS REAR WHEEL', 'buy ZIPP 303 NSW CARBON TUBELESS REAR WHEEL from Toracycles 100% Original', 'ZIPP 303 NSW CARBON TUBELESS REAR WHEEL'),
